{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantTypeT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"kind":"text","text":">("},{"text":"type","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VariantTypeT"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"VariantTypeT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VariantTypeProtocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantTypeProtocol","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib19VariantTypeProtocolP"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type"},{"text":" must be non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":".  It specifies the type of container to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"construct.  It can be an indefinite type such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_ARRAY","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or a definite type such as “as” or “(ii)”.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Maybe, array, tuple, dictionary entry and variant-typed values may be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constructed."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If using a static type such as one of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE_*"},{"type":"text","text":" constants"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or a ","type":"text"},{"code":"G_VARIANT_TYPE (\"(ii)\")","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" macro, it is more performant to use","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_builder_init_static()"},{"type":"text","text":" rather than "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_builder_init()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After the builder is initialised, values are added using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_builder_add_value()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_builder_add()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After all the child values are added, ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_variant_builder_end()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" frees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the memory associated with the builder and returns the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"was created."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This function completely ignores the previous contents of ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"builder"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"On one hand this means that it is valid to pass in completely"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"uninitialised memory.  On the other hand, this means that if you are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initialising over top of an existing "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantBuilder"},{"text":" you need to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"first call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_builder_clear()"},{"text":" in order to avoid leaking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"memory.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You must not call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_builder_ref()"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_builder_unref()"},{"text":" on a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantBuilder","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" that was initialised"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with this function.  If you ever pass a reference to a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantBuilder","isActive":true},{"text":" outside of the control of your own code then you","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"should assume that the person receiving that reference may try to use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reference counting; you should use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_builder_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" instead of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this function."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"extendedModule":"GLib","title":"init_(type:)","role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"VariantTypeT","kind":"genericParameter"},{"text":">(","kind":"text"},{"text":"type","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariantTypeT","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib22VariantBuilderProtocolPAAE5init_4typeyqd___tAA0b4TypeD0Rd__lF","symbolKind":"method"},"abstract":[{"text":"Initialises a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantBuilder","isActive":true},{"text":" structure.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/variantbuilderprotocol\/init_(type:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation